article.headline: Anderson scores 21 as Lamar downs Houston Christian 78-68

images.name: Ja'Sean Jackson lobs it off the backboard for a dunk
images.caption: Ja'Sean Jackson passes it off the backboard to Terry Anderson, who flushes home the rock with authority.

article.linkText: Anderson scores 21 as Lamar downs Houston Christian 78-68
article.story: BEAUMONT, Texas -- — Terry Anderson scored 21 points and Lamar beat Houston Christian 78-68 on Wednesday night. Anderson also had five rebounds for the Cardinals (18-13, 12-6 Southland Conference). Chris Pryor hit three 3-pointers and scored 15. Cody Pennebaker pitched in with 10 points, five rebounds and four steals. Marcus Greene and Jay Alvarez both scored 17 to lead the Huskies (6-23, 4-14), who have lost seven straight. Greene added seven rebounds. Bonke Maring finished with 16 points, 12 rebounds and three steals. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
